WEBVTT

00:00:28.125 --> 00:00:30.333
Hey, you're here early.

00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:34.917
--As always, business is slow here.
--Shut up.

00:00:34.917 --> 00:00:36.792
It's busy at night.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.917
So that picture...
what's the deal with that?

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:49.333
It's kind of a long story.

00:00:50.042 --> 00:00:51.875
Ever hear of this?

00:00:54.333 --> 00:00:55.500
A game?

00:00:55.500 --> 00:01:00.500
It's an MMO for the Amusphere,
a successor to the NerveGear.

00:01:01.042 --> 00:01:05.375
Then another virtual MMO like SAO?

00:01:05.875 --> 00:01:08.542
Alf Heim Online?

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.083
It's pronounced "Alv-heim," supposedly.

00:01:12.083 --> 00:01:15.542
They say it means
"Land of the Fairies."

00:01:15.542 --> 00:01:17.083
Fairies?

00:01:21.542 --> 00:01:27.000
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:32.375
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:01:42.708 --> 00:01:53.042
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:01:53.167 --> 00:02:03.750
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:02:03.875 --> 00:02:09.083
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:02:09.083 --> 00:02:12.917
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:19.250
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:19.458 --> 00:02:24.333
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:30.000
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:36.167
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:02:38.042 --> 00:02:44.583
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:02:50.083 --> 00:02:54.083
"Land of the Fairies"

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.833
Land of the Fairies?

00:02:57.292 --> 00:03:01.583
--It's the laid-back kind then?
--No, not from what I hear.

00:03:03.042 --> 00:03:07.750
It's a hard-core skill system focusing
on player skill. PKing is encouraged.

00:03:07.750 --> 00:03:12.125
--Hard-core skill system?
--No actual levels, as such.

00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:18.792
Each skill only improves through use.
Combat relies on players' athletic ability.

00:03:18.792 --> 00:03:20.625
That is hard core.

00:03:20.625 --> 00:03:24.750
Like an SAO with magic
but no sword skills.

00:03:24.750 --> 00:03:30.333
I hear it's insanely popular now.
I've heard it's because you can fly.

00:03:30.333 --> 00:03:33.875
--Fly?
--You're a fairy, so you have wings.

00:03:33.875 --> 00:03:39.500
It has something called a "flight engine,"
and once you get used to it, you can fly at will.

00:03:39.833 --> 00:03:42.917
--How do you control it?
--Who knows?

00:03:42.917 --> 00:03:45.458
But I hear it's pretty hard.

00:03:45.458 --> 00:03:50.458
Sure, no kidding. You're controlling
wings that no human has.

00:03:50.458 --> 00:03:53.625
Maybe you use
the muscles on your back?

00:03:55.375 --> 00:04:00.250
So what does this popular game
have to do with Asuna?

00:04:02.333 --> 00:04:04.292
What do you think?

00:04:04.875 --> 00:04:07.750
It looks like her. Like Asuna.

00:04:07.750 --> 00:04:12.667
--I thought you'd say that.
--Just tell me. Where is this?

00:04:12.667 --> 00:04:16.167
Inside the game. In ALfheim Online.

00:04:17.917 --> 00:04:21.208
It's called the World Tree, I hear.

00:04:21.208 --> 00:04:24.833
A legendary castle sits atop this tree.

00:04:24.833 --> 00:04:27.833
Players are divided into nine races,

00:04:27.833 --> 00:04:32.167
all of them racing
to reach the castle first.

00:04:32.417 --> 00:04:34.500
Can't they fly there?

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:39.000
Supposedly, there's a time limit,
so you can't fly forever.

00:04:39.292 --> 00:04:45.000
So five players got on each other's shoulders
and flew up like a rocket.

00:04:46.542 --> 00:04:49.958
I get it... It's dumb, but pretty smart.

00:04:50.458 --> 00:04:54.417
And they didn't even make it
to the tree's lowest branch,

00:04:54.417 --> 00:04:59.833
but they did take a few pictures.
And something strange was in one.

00:05:01.083 --> 00:05:02.542
A birdcage?

00:05:02.542 --> 00:05:07.333
And when they zoomed in on
the cage as tight as they could,

00:05:07.333 --> 00:05:09.292
they found this.

00:05:09.292 --> 00:05:12.958
But why would Asuna
be in a place like that?

00:05:14.250 --> 00:05:16.542
RCT Progress?

00:05:17.833 --> 00:05:22.542
You could say I'm the one
who's keeping Asuna alive.

00:05:25.917 --> 00:05:29.042
Agil, mind if I take this software?

00:05:29.042 --> 00:05:34.750
--I don't, but do you plan to go there?
--I need to see for myself.

00:05:34.750 --> 00:05:37.750
A game where
you can die is too easy.

00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:47.208
--I'll have to buy the hardware.
--It works with NerveGear.

00:05:47.208 --> 00:05:51.708
The Amusphere is just
NerveGear with better security.

00:05:51.708 --> 00:05:53.542
Glad to hear it.

00:05:53.542 --> 00:05:55.667
Go save Asuna.

00:05:56.042 --> 00:05:59.458
Otherwise our battle won't really end.

00:05:59.792 --> 00:06:03.417
Yeah, let's all meet here someday.

00:06:18.333 --> 00:06:20.792
I'm so stupid, stupid, stupid!

00:06:20.792 --> 00:06:22.042
I'm back.

00:06:22.958 --> 00:06:25.000
B-Big Brother!

00:06:37.208 --> 00:06:38.458
Here.

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:47.417
--I-I thought I was going to die.
--You're so careless.

00:06:47.417 --> 00:06:50.250
Eat slowly, will you?

00:06:51.708 --> 00:06:55.792
--Sugu, about last night...
--Y-Yeah?

00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:58.625
Um... Well...

00:06:59.250 --> 00:07:00.667
Thank you.

00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:04.792
Thanks to you, Sugu, I feel better.

00:07:04.792 --> 00:07:09.500
I won't give up.
I'm going to get Asuna back.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:16.792
Good luck. I want to meet her too.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:22.500
I'm sure you'll like her.
Okay, I'll see you later.

00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:44.000
The ceremony will be held in this
hospital room in a week, on January 26th.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.083
I'll invite you.

00:07:46.417 --> 00:07:49.875
Please help me one more time.

00:08:01.542 --> 00:08:03.042
Link start!

00:08:15.167 --> 00:08:17.958
<i>Welcome to ALfheim Online.</i>

00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:24.375
<i>First, enter your gender</i>
<i>and character name.</i>

00:08:27.083 --> 00:08:30.833
Really? So you're the hero Kirito?

00:08:41.375 --> 00:08:44.000
<i>Now, select your race.</i>

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.125
<i>Please select one of the nine races.</i>

00:08:50.875 --> 00:08:53.250
Why don't I take this one?

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.583
<i>Spriggan, correct?</i>

00:08:55.583 --> 00:09:00.333
<i>Your character's appearance will be</i>
<i>decided at random. Is that all right?</i>

00:09:02.583 --> 00:09:06.792
<i>You will now be transferred to</i>
<i>the hometown in Spriggan territory.</i>

00:09:06.792 --> 00:09:08.375
<i>Good luck.</i>

00:09:34.917 --> 00:09:36.333
What?

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.958
What's going on?!

00:09:53.500 --> 00:09:58.833
"ALfheim, Neutral Territory, Ancient Forest
January 20, 2025"

00:10:13.542 --> 00:10:15.417
I'm back...

00:10:17.333 --> 00:10:19.875
After everything that happened.

00:10:22.042 --> 00:10:24.458
Wait, where am I?

00:10:35.083 --> 00:10:36.667
It's there.

00:10:36.667 --> 00:10:37.750
"You cannot instantly log out in the field.
Is that all right?"

00:10:42.417 --> 00:10:45.250
Now, where's the status window?

00:10:47.708 --> 00:10:51.333
What is this? Is it a bug?

00:10:51.333 --> 00:10:53.292
"One-Handed Sword"
"????"
"Thrown Weapon"

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:58.417
They're the same
as my SAO parameters...

00:10:59.375 --> 00:11:01.375
What's going on?

00:11:01.375 --> 00:11:04.083
Is this inside SAO?

00:11:12.375 --> 00:11:13.792
Hold on...

00:11:14.625 --> 00:11:17.708
Come on... Please be here...

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:04.167
It's me, Yui!
Do you remember me?

00:12:08.375 --> 00:12:12.000
I got to see you again, Daddy...

00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:14.667
Yui...

00:12:16.875 --> 00:12:18.083
Mommy!

00:12:18.083 --> 00:12:20.792
You must be hungry! Let's eat.

00:12:20.792 --> 00:12:21.958
Yeah!

00:12:29.375 --> 00:12:30.458
It's good...

00:12:31.042 --> 00:12:33.417
Mommy... Daddy...

00:12:35.958 --> 00:12:37.208
Daddy!

00:12:37.458 --> 00:12:38.542
Daddy!

00:12:40.292 --> 00:12:41.500
Daddy...

00:12:43.667 --> 00:12:46.500
Miracles really do happen.

00:12:58.083 --> 00:13:01.458
So what's going on here, exactly?

00:13:02.833 --> 00:13:05.958
See... We aren't inside SAO.

00:13:06.417 --> 00:13:10.750
This is the world of another game
called ALfheim Online.

00:13:11.417 --> 00:13:13.833
Hold on a second.

00:13:15.375 --> 00:13:20.542
This world seems to be a copy
of the Sword Art Online servers.

00:13:20.833 --> 00:13:22.042
A copy?

00:13:22.042 --> 00:13:23.208
Yes.

00:13:23.208 --> 00:13:27.833
The game engine and graphics format
are completely identical.

00:13:27.833 --> 00:13:32.667
Although the version of
the Cardinal system is a little outdated.

00:13:34.208 --> 00:13:39.625
RCT took over operations from Argus,
the company that originally ran SAO.

00:13:39.625 --> 00:13:45.875
In other words, RCT absorbed Argus's
technological assets and diverted them.

00:13:45.875 --> 00:13:49.167
But why is my personal data here?

00:13:49.417 --> 00:13:53.250
Let me have a look at your data, Daddy.

00:13:55.167 --> 00:13:57.208
There's no question.

00:13:57.208 --> 00:14:01.750
This is definitely the character data
you used in SAO.

00:14:02.042 --> 00:14:05.417
The save-data format
is nearly the same,

00:14:05.417 --> 00:14:10.458
so skills common to both games
must've had their levels overwritten.

00:14:10.458 --> 00:14:13.917
Come to think of it,
my dual-wielding was gone.

00:14:13.917 --> 00:14:17.958
Your items appear to be lost, as well.

00:14:17.958 --> 00:14:22.458
You should delete them before
the error-detection program finds them.

00:14:22.458 --> 00:14:23.792
I see.

00:14:27.167 --> 00:14:29.625
"Do you want to delete all items?"

00:14:40.875 --> 00:14:43.917
Now, what about my skill levels?

00:14:43.917 --> 00:14:49.833
Your skills shouldn't be a problem unless
a human game master sees them firsthand.

00:14:50.250 --> 00:14:51.875
O-Okay...

00:14:53.083 --> 00:14:57.250
I'm not a beater anymore.
I'm just a cheater.

00:14:57.792 --> 00:15:00.917
What are you being recognized as?

00:15:00.917 --> 00:15:06.167
Um, I'm listed as a player-support
artificial-personality program,

00:15:06.167 --> 00:15:09.042
a Navigation Pixie.

00:15:10.625 --> 00:15:12.208
H-Hey!

00:15:20.333 --> 00:15:23.167
This is my form as a pixie.

00:15:25.667 --> 00:15:27.292
That tickles.

00:15:27.292 --> 00:15:31.667
Then do you still have
admin privileges like before?

00:15:31.667 --> 00:15:37.583
No. All I can do is access the reference
and wide-area-map databases.

00:15:37.583 --> 00:15:39.000
I see.

00:15:39.708 --> 00:15:44.917
Actually, it seems that Asuna...
Your mommy is here.

00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:48.833
Mommy? What do you mean?

00:15:49.250 --> 00:15:54.750
Even after SAO was cleared,
Asuna never woke up in reality.

00:15:54.750 --> 00:15:59.583
I heard that someone who looked
like Asuna was seen in ALfheim.

00:15:59.917 --> 00:16:02.292
So that's what happened...

00:16:02.292 --> 00:16:07.375
I have a good idea of where to look.
It's called the World Tree.

00:16:08.042 --> 00:16:10.042
I think that's it.

00:16:10.042 --> 00:16:12.500
Mommy is over there?

00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:22.000
Actually, why did I log in
at this empty forest?

00:16:22.625 --> 00:16:26.125
I was supposed to be
teleported to the hometown...

00:16:26.125 --> 00:16:32.042
I don't know. Your location data got corrupted?
Or there was interference?

00:16:32.292 --> 00:16:37.125
I wish it would've at least
dropped me near the World Tree.

00:16:40.583 --> 00:16:43.458
These are the wings, huh?

00:16:43.458 --> 00:16:45.458
How do I fly?

00:16:46.083 --> 00:16:50.125
There seems to be an assist controller.
Raise your left hand

00:16:50.125 --> 00:16:53.208
as if you're grabbing something.

00:16:57.542 --> 00:17:01.875
Um, pull toward yourself
to ascend. Push to descend.

00:17:01.875 --> 00:17:04.292
Left or right to turn.

00:17:09.083 --> 00:17:14.250
Hold down the button to accelerate.
Release to decelerate, apparently.

00:17:16.958 --> 00:17:20.583
You can fly as long
as your wings are shining.

00:17:21.167 --> 00:17:25.500
After a certain amount of time,
you need to rest your wings.

00:17:32.833 --> 00:17:35.542
I see. I think I've got it.

00:17:35.542 --> 00:17:38.708
For now, where's the closest town?

00:17:39.167 --> 00:17:43.542
There's a town in Sylph territory
called Sylvain to the west.

00:17:43.542 --> 00:17:45.542
That's the closest...

00:17:46.792 --> 00:17:50.417
--What's wrong?
--There are players nearby.

00:18:07.625 --> 00:18:10.833
L-Leafa, wait!

00:18:11.292 --> 00:18:15.750
You can do it, Recon!
If we can escape to Sylph territory...

00:18:16.292 --> 00:18:17.917
Recon, dodge!

00:18:21.292 --> 00:18:23.625
Back off, already!

00:18:24.667 --> 00:18:25.917
No choice then.

00:18:26.833 --> 00:18:29.167
Prepare for battle!

00:18:29.167 --> 00:18:33.417
Impossible! I'm sure Sigurd
and the others are already...

00:18:33.417 --> 00:18:37.833
I'll draw in as many as I can,
so knock at least one down.

00:18:37.833 --> 00:18:39.708
I'll do my best.

00:18:39.708 --> 00:18:43.292
Show me how useful
you can be for once, okay?

00:19:03.167 --> 00:19:04.583
Damn it!

00:19:14.417 --> 00:19:16.333
<i>We can win this.</i>

00:19:19.333 --> 00:19:21.167
Idiot! Don't stop!

00:19:22.792 --> 00:19:24.250
Sorry!

00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:27.625
Recon...

00:19:57.250 --> 00:19:58.333
Sorry,

00:19:58.625 --> 00:20:03.583
but we're on a mission. Leave your
money and items, and we'll let you go.

00:20:03.583 --> 00:20:06.167
Why the gentleman act, Kagemune?

00:20:06.167 --> 00:20:10.000
It's been ages since we
fought a woman. Let's kill her.

00:20:12.625 --> 00:20:15.875
I'm taking at least one of you with me.

00:20:15.875 --> 00:20:19.333
Anyone who doesn't fear
the death penalty can attack!

00:20:19.333 --> 00:20:22.875
You're a strong-willed girl.
No choice, then.

00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:53.833
I still have to work on landing, huh?

00:20:59.292 --> 00:21:01.375
What are you doing? Run!

00:21:02.167 --> 00:21:06.083
Three heavy fighters
attacking a single girl?

00:21:06.083 --> 00:21:08.125
That's kind of lame.

00:21:08.125 --> 00:21:12.250
--What did you say?
--You've got some nerve, newbie.

00:21:16.667 --> 00:21:20.542
Since you're asking for it,
I'll fight you!

00:21:36.875 --> 00:21:38.292
Um...

00:21:38.458 --> 00:21:41.667
Is it okay if I kill those guys?

00:21:42.333 --> 00:21:45.167
I-I guess so...

00:21:45.542 --> 00:21:49.000
At least, that's what
they intended for you.

00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:51.833
All right then. Pardon me.

00:21:59.833 --> 00:22:01.250
He's disappeared!

00:22:14.792 --> 00:22:16.542
Who's next?

00:22:17.917 --> 00:22:25.042
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.042 --> 00:22:34.917
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.125 --> 00:22:52.875
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.208 --> 00:23:00.083
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.417 --> 00:23:07.292
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.458 --> 00:23:15.208
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:22.167
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.167 --> 00:23:29.333
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.333 --> 00:23:36.708
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:44.958
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "Captive Queen."
